# Session Manager Widget

A centered popup triggered by `/session` (no args) showing all saved sessions. Users can navigate with arrow keys, press Enter to load a session, or hover/navigate to reveal and click a delete button.

## Design Decisions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Not extending [BasePopupListView](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/views/common/popup_list.py#37-280)** — The existing popup base is designed for bottom-docked, fuzzy-filtered, trigger-character popups (`/`, `@`). The session manager is a **centered modal** with a **grid layout** (name + delete column), no search bar, and different interaction semantics. A new standalone widget is cleaner than forcing it into the existing abstraction.

> [!NOTE]
> **Trigger mechanism** — The popup is opened from the command handler via an event. When `/session` is submitted without args, the handler publishes a `SessionPopupRequestEvent` (a new lightweight event). The app listens for this event and calls `session_popup.open()`. This keeps the command handler decoupled from the TUI.

## Proposed Changes

### Events

#### [MODIFY] [events.py](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/core/events/events.py)

Add a new `SessionPopupRequestEvent(BaseEvent)` — a zero-payload event that signals the TUI to open the session manager popup.

---

### Session Manager Widget

#### [NEW] [session_popup.py](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/views/common/session_popup.py)

A new `SessionPopup(Widget)` that renders as a centered overlay.

**CSS:**
- `layer: overlay`, `display: none`, centered via `align: center middle` on parent or absolute positioning
- Fixed width (~60 cols), height auto with max-height
- `background: $surface`, `border: solid $primary`

**Layout per row (CSS Grid):**
```
| Name or ID (1fr)                    | delete (auto) |
```
- Single-line per entry, no margin between rows
- Name column: shows `session.name` if present, else `session.session_id`
- Delete column: `[lightcoral]delete[/]`, right-aligned, **hidden by default**, visible only when the row is selected (via keyboard nav) or hovered (via mouse)

**Behavior:**
- [open(sessions: List[SessionSummary])](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/app.py#140-148) — populate and show
- `close()` — hide and reset
- Arrow keys ↑/↓ move selection, Enter loads the selected session, Esc closes
- Delete click/action removes the session from the list and calls manager.delete()
- Posts `SessionPopup.SessionLoaded(session_id)` message on selection
- Posts `SessionPopup.SessionDeleted(session_id)` message on delete

---

### Command Handler Integration

#### [MODIFY] [session.py](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/commands/handlers/session.py)

Change the no-args branch (line 29-30). Instead of returning usage text:
```diff
     if not args:
-        return CommandResult(success=False, message=_usage())
+        if ctx.event_bus:
+            await ctx.event_bus.publish(SessionPopupRequestEvent(source="cmd_session"))
+        return CommandResult(success=True, message="")
```

This publishes the event so the TUI can react, while returning an empty success result (no message shown in chat).

---

### App Integration

#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/app.py)

1. Import and instantiate `SessionPopup`
2. Yield it in [compose()](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/views/footer/footer.py#68-75) alongside other popups
3. Subscribe to `SessionPopupRequestEvent` → call `session_popup.open(manager.list())`
4. Handle `SessionPopup.SessionLoaded` message → delegate to [_cmd_session_restore](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/commands/handlers/session.py#101-143) logic
5. Handle `SessionPopup.SessionDeleted` message → delegate to `manager.delete()`

---

### Tests

#### [NEW] [test_session_popup.py](file:///x:/agent_cli/tests/session/test_session_popup.py)

Unit tests covering:
- [open()](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/ux/tui/app.py#140-148) populates items from a list of [SessionSummary](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/session/base.py#30-41)
- Selecting an entry posts `SessionLoaded` with correct [session_id](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/commands/handlers/session.py#253-274)
- Deleting an entry posts `SessionDeleted` with correct [session_id](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/commands/handlers/session.py#253-274)
- Name fallback: shows [session_id](file:///x:/agent_cli/agent_cli/commands/handlers/session.py#253-274) when `name is None`
- Esc closes the popup

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

```bash
# Run existing session tests (must still pass)
python -m pytest tests/session/ -v

# Run new popup tests
python -m pytest tests/session/test_session_popup.py -v
```

### Manual Verification

Launch the TUI and type `/session` + Enter (with no subcommand). The centered popup should appear with a list of saved sessions. Verify:
1. Each row shows name (or id if unnamed) and a hidden delete button
2. Arrow keys navigate, Enter loads, Esc dismisses
3. Hovering / selecting a row reveals the red "delete" text on the right
